    "narrative": "For April 14, **Corbin Carroll** stands out as the clear anchor of our lineup with a 75.35 score. His favorable matchup against Trevor Rogers\u2014combined with a massive +16% park adjustment and an aggressive +8% bump for batting second\u2014positions him as our primary engine for Runs and SB today. **James Wood** also earns an elite designation (66.50) leading off against Mitch Keller, where his volume potential at the top of the order outweighs the neutral platoon advantage. Meanwhile, **Jose Caballero** remains a high-upside play for his speed, despite a dip in raw projection caused by Reid Detmers\u2019 efficiency; his +13% platoon edge against a lefty makes him a vital, if volatile, asset in our pursuit of stolen bases.\n\nWe have strategically opted to bench **Giancarlo Stanton** (50.28) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (47.09) in favor of players who offer a higher floor for daily efficiency. **Giancarlo Stanton** was the most difficult exclusion, as the wind-out conditions in his game favored his power profile, but he ultimately lacks the categorical versatility we require to push our league standing. Conversely, we are steering clear of **Zach McKinstry** and **Alex Freeland**, both of whom fell below our 40.0 \"Zebras Floor\" due to tough matchups against elite arms like Cole Ragans. While **Max Muncy** and **Tyler Soderstrom** have to navigate the skill set of Gore, both remain strong starts (57.09 and 57.66 respectively) largely due to park factors that keep them comfortably above our threshold for daily usage. \n\nRegarding risks, we are monitoring the catcher framing and high-end pitch mix of the opposing staff. **Seiya Suzuki** (54.90) faces a slight drag from a tough catcher matchup (1.86s pop time), but the wind blowing out at his park keeps him firmly in our starting nine. As we look at the broader roster, including **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Mickey Moniak**, **Gabriel Moreno**, **Dalton Rushing**, **Carson Williams**, and **Travis Bazzana**, we are satisfied with today's configuration. Our focus remains on maintaining our lead in SB without sacrificing the efficiency of our total plate appearances.",
